tweet: The AGO outlines three prohibited categories that violate civil rights laws: racial segregation, race stereotyping, and race scapegoating. Schools, other governmental entities, and employers may not engage in activities that fall under these categories. (5/6)

name: Austin Knudsen
tweet: Many activities undertaken in the name of CRT violate federal and state law and are therefore prohibited in Montana. This includes but is not limited to things like “privilege walks” based on race and employers telling their employees to be “less white.” (4/6)

tweet: Montana law does not tolerate schools, other government entities, or employers implementing CRT and antiracist programming in a way that treats individuals differently on the basis of race or that creates a racially hostile environment. (3/6)
